Ambulance LTD - Stay Where You Are:
The strumming pattern is important for the feel of the song but I have trouble transcribing strumming
so listen to the song to make sure you're getting the right timing. Essentially you want to hit the B chord
hard once before switching to the E and then just hit the D#m(b6) once in passing before going back to B.

[Chords]

[tab]B:       7-9-9-8-7-7
E:       x-7-9-9-9-7
D#m(b6): x-6-9-8-7-6
F#:      x-9-11-11-11-9[/tab]

[tab]B7sus: 7-9-7-9-7-7[/tab]

The B7sus is totally optional but really gives flavor to the song. You only have to lift your pinky while
playing the B and move it two strings down for a second or two and then back up to the regular B and voila
you've played a B7sus.

Throughout the song you can also slide a half-step up into the B before switching to the E which you'll hear
them do in the song quite a bit. So start on A# and slide one fret up into the B for a downstroke and then off
to E. You can just hit the lowest string for this half-step slide and pretty much achieve the desired effect.
